  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 53647,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "elber discovered a CSRF in webapp.starbucks.co.jp leaked an access token if an authenticated user opened a crafted HTML file in a browser other than Chrome which has Same Site Attribute for the cookie set by default.\n\nelber also demonstrated the ability to add a Starbucks card to the account with the potential for a single account takeover at login.starbucks.co.jp, if the attacker could trick the user into executing another crafted HTML file.\n\nelber — thank you for reporting this vulnerability and for confirming the resolution.\n",
